body:
@alexbrainman I'll look into it, thanks for the link. My plan in general is best effort with limited scope. I think even partial improvement with backwards compatibility is a success.

@minux that's exactly the *magic* that I was talking about in my previous post. I agree that it would be nice to support relative paths etc, but that's not something I'm too excited about solving right now. Paths longer than MAX_PATH don't work right now at all. Adding support for long full paths seems easy and I don't think support for them should be held back by the lack of support for long relative paths. Again, I don't plan on changing behavior of paths shorter than MAX_PATH, so relative paths there will continue to work just fine.

I haven't written the changes yet, they're only theoretical based on brief reviews of the Go source & my knowledge of the Windows API. I hope to get some practical testing done soon.
